{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "This PR adds two new components:\r\n\r\n* `JointPositionReset`\r\n* `JointVelocityReset`\r\n\r\nThese components act directly on the physics engine, resetting the simulation state of the selected joint. As discussed in [PR#246](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/246/add-jointcontroller-system/diff), the usage of this feature should not be encouraged since fiddling with the internal state of the simulator generally is not a good practice. Though, if done responsibly, it is a feature that has diverse use cases.\r\n\r\nAs an example, it is currently possible to insert a model in a running simulation with a given pose. However, I didn\u2019t find any way to apply also a specific joint configuration. These new components allow to obtain such state.\r\n\r\nThere\u2019s also downstream code of Gazebo Classic that use this features and might need in the future to reset the joint state.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This PR adds two new components:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>JointPositionReset</code></li>\n<li><code>JointVelocityReset</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>These components act directly on the physics engine, resetting the simulation state of the selected joint. As discussed in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/246/add-jointcontroller-system/diff\" rel=\"nofollow\">PR#246</a>, the usage of this feature should not be encouraged since fiddling with the internal state of the simulator generally is not a good practice. Though, if done responsibly, it is a feature that has diverse use cases.</p>\n<p>As an example, it is currently possible to insert a model in a running simulation with a given pose. However, I didn\u2019t find any way to apply also a specific joint configuration. These new components allow to obtain such state.</p>\n<p>There\u2019s also downstream code of Gazebo Classic that use this features and might need in the future to reset the joint state.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "JointPositionReset and JointVelocityReset components", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>JointPositionReset and JointVelocityReset components</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "This PR adds two new components:\r\n\r\n* `JointPositionReset`\r\n* `JointVelocityReset`\r\n\r\nThese components act directly on the physics engine, resetting the simulation state of the selected joint. As discussed in [PR#246](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/246/add-jointcontroller-system/diff), the usage of this feature should not be encouraged since fiddling with the internal state of the simulator generally is not a good practice. Though, if done responsibly, it is a feature that has diverse use cases.\r\n\r\nAs an example, it is currently possible to insert a model in a running simulation with a given pose. However, I didn\u2019t find any way to apply also a specific joint configuration. These new components allow to obtain such state.\r\n\r\nThere\u2019s also downstream code of Gazebo Classic that use this features and might need in the future to reset the joint state.", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/decline"}, "diffstat": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diffstat/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:b52c1de07808%0Dad8a6ce72565?from_pullrequest_id=437"}, "commits": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/commits.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437.json"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/comments_page=1.json"}, "merge": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/merge"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/437"}, "activity": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/activity.json"}, "diff": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:b52c1de07808%0Dad8a6ce72565?from_pullrequest_id=437"}, "approve": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/approve"}, "statuses": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/437/statuses_page=1.json"}}, "title": "JointPositionReset and JointVelocityReset components", "close_source_branch": false, "reviewers": [{"display_name": "Addisu Z. Taddese", "uuid": "{9d7fdc68-d270-4080-bf03-4df0d0dbf635}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B9d7fdc68-d270-4080-bf03-4df0d0dbf635%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B9d7fdc68-d270-4080-bf03-4df0d0dbf635%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:90bc87b0-2886-4377-a17c-3a6629a697ff/afbf9be5-1e4c-4810-89d4-e58831f34b11/128"}}, "nickname": "azeey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:90bc87b0-2886-4377-a17c-3a6629a697ff"}, {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9/d42d74cf-c1bd-4431-8288-07f543bbe325/128"}}, "nickname": "mxgrey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:67759e29-d1df-465f-868d-047738e36fc9"}, {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-managem