et</code></li>\n<li><code>JointVelocityReset</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>These components act directly on the physics engine, resetting the simulation state of the selected joint. As discussed in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/246/add-jointcontroller-system/diff\" rel=\"nofollow\">PR#246</a>, the usage of this feature should not be encouraged since fiddling with the internal state of the simulator generally is not a good practice. Though, if done responsibly, it is a feature that has diverse use cases.</p>\n<p>As an example, it is currently possible to insert a model in a running simulation with a given pose. However, I didn\u2019t find any way to apply also a specific joint configuration. These new components allow to obtain such state.</p>\n<p>There\u2019s also downstream code of Gazebo Classic that use this features and might need in the future to reset the joint state.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "source": {"commit": {"hash": "a95d8429b64d", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/dgferigo/ign-gazebo/commit/a95d8429b64d"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/dgferigo/ign-gazebo/commits/a95d8429b64d"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/dgferigo/ign-gazebo"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/dgferigo/ign-gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{23f4ff40-6a14-44ea-848a-367cfbd3bb51}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "ign-gazebo", "full_name": "dgferigo/ign-gazebo", "uuid": "{23f4ff40-6a14-44ea-848a-367cfbd3bb51}"}, "branch": {"name": "reset-joint"}}, "comment_count": 44, "state": "MERGED", "task_count": 0, "participants": [{"role": "PARTICIPANT", "participated_on": "2020-03-16T17:45:51.442358+00:00", "type": "participant", "approved": false, "user": {"display_name": "Diego Ferigo", "uuid": "{994b27a5-7d6d-42b2-8aa7-2ea82fbe7bf6}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bit